<p>Minnesota's solar resource potential often surprises those unfamiliar with the state's renewable energy capabilities. With 4.3 peak sun hours per day annually, Minnesota ranks favorably among U.S. states for solar energy production. The state's northern latitude is offset by long summer days, clear winter weather, and the efficiency benefits of cooler temperatures on solar panel performance. Solar panels actually operate more efficiently in cooler weather, making Minnesota's climate advantageous for consistent energy production throughout the year.</p>

